OL,7,FThe court heard it was the prosecution
OL,8,Fcase that he had lost his temper and
OL,9,Fdeliberately kicked his partner
OL,10,Fcausing her to "fly backwards" down
OL,11,Fthe stairs and break her back. Orphan
OL,12,Fhad denied that, saying it was his
OL,13,Fwife who had lost her temper, not him.
OL,15,FThe prosecution also accused Orphan of
OL,16,Fthreatening his wife that she wouldn't
OL,17,Fsee her children if she did not say
OL,18,Fthe right things to doctors about how
OL,19,Fthe back injury had been caused, which
OL,20,Fhe denied.
