OL,7,FThe incident on the stairs took place
OL,8,Fas the couple argued. Orphan claimed
OL,9,Fhis wife had thrown a child seat at
OL,10,Fhim and, as he climbed the stairs, she
OL,11,Fgrabbed his leg causing him to
OL,12,Fstumble. He claimed that his leg made
OL,13,Fcontact with her waist as he tried to
OL,14,Ftake evasive action to "haul myself to
OL,15,Fsafety". The defendant accepted that
OL,16,Fin doing this his leg made contact
OL,17,Fwith his partner's waist causing her
OL,18,Fto fall down the stairs, but denied
OL,19,Fthat his action was deliberate. The
OL,20,Fprosecution's case was that this was a
OL,21,Fdeliberate act.
